  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A binding requirement mandates experimental-validation as the required verification method for hemolysis output comparison; however, the supporting validation activity was carried out as a literature-review of published hemolysis correlations and prior computational studies. The narrative presents the literature review as complementary evidence that corroborates CFD predictions, but the structured activityType does not satisfy the required verification method, creating an inference method mismatch under W-AR-03.",
